    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Film movement began in Italy near the end of World War II, typified by the use of both professional and non-professional actors, ordinary settings and themes, and the rejection of the happy-ending story. The films tend to focus on social issues and the everyday problems of its characters.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047993/Konigsberg, The Complete Film Dictionary (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>二次世界大戰後起源自義大利的電影運動，其特色為同時啟用職業和非職業演員、採用日常實景和主題，以及抗拒圓滿的結局。這類型電影聚焦反映著社會議題，以及片中角色所面對的日常生活問題。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Filmstroming die begon in Italië tegen het einde van de Tweede Wereldoorlog en die wordt gekenmerkt door het gebruik van zowel professionele als niet-professionele acteurs, alledaagse omgevingen en thema's, en een afkeer voor verhalen met een happy end. De films gaan vaak over sociale kwesties en de alledaagse beslommeringen van de personages.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>O movimento cinematográfico começou na Itália perto do final da Segunda Guerra Mundial, caracterizado pelo uso de atores profissionais e não profissionais, cenários e temas comuns e a rejeição da história com final feliz. Os filmes tendem a focar em questões sociais e nos problemas cotidianos de seus personagens. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
